Sentencas: The effect of firing temperature on the microstructure and performance of PrBaCo2O5+delta cathodes on Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 electrolytes fabricated by spray deposition-firing processes is systematically studied by various characterization techniques.
Titulo: Effect of firing temperature on the microstructure and performance of PrBaCo2O5+δ cathodes on Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 electrolytes fabricated by spray deposition-firing processes

Sentencas: The grain size, porosity and particle connection of the electrode as well as the physical contact between the PrBaCo2O5+delta and Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 layers are influenced differently by the firing temperature.
Titulo: Effect of firing temperature on the microstructure and performance of PrBaCo2O5+δ cathodes on Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 electrolytes fabricated by spray deposition-firing processes

Sentencas: The area specific resistances (ASRs) of the various PrBaCo2O5+delta cathodes are measured by electrochemical impedance spectroscopy in both symmetrical two-electrode and three-electrode configurations.
Titulo: Effect of firing temperature on the microstructure and performance of PrBaCo2O5+δ cathodes on Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 electrolytes fabricated by spray deposition-firing processes

Sentencas: The lowest ASR and cathode overpotential are achieved at a firing temperature of 1000 degrees C. Two main oxygen reduction reaction processes are proposed according to the oxygen partial pressure dependence of the electrode ASR.
Titulo: Effect of firing temperature on the microstructure and performance of PrBaCo2O5+δ cathodes on Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 electrolytes fabricated by spray deposition-firing processes

Sentencas: The rate-determining step is transmitted from a charge-transfer process at low firing temperatures to a non-charge-transfer process at high firing temperatures.
Titulo: Effect of firing temperature on the microstructure and performance of PrBaCo2O5+δ cathodes on Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 electrolytes fabricated by spray deposition-firing processes

Sentencas: A fuel cell with the PrBaCo2O5+delta cathode fired at an optimal temperature of 1000 degrees C delivers the attractive peak power density of 835 mW cm(-2) at 650 degrees C. while this density is much lower for other firing temperatures.
Titulo: Effect of firing temperature on the microstructure and performance of PrBaCo2O5+δ cathodes on Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 electrolytes fabricated by spray deposition-firing processes

Sentencas: This result suggests the firing temperature of PrBaCo2O5+delta electrodes should be carefully optimized for practical applications.
Titulo: Effect of firing temperature on the microstructure and performance of PrBaCo2O5+δ cathodes on Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 electrolytes fabricated by spray deposition-firing processes
